              <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td><span class="module-label">1.1 Basic concepts</span></td>
                <td>
                  <ul class="topic-list">
                    <li>Network types: LAN, WAN, MAN, small office network</li>
                    <li>Client and server, peer-to-peer</li>
                    <li>Throughput, latency, bandwidth, jitter (concept)</li>
                  </ul>
                </td>
                <td><span class="level-pill">Beginner</span></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><span class="module-label">1.2 Topologies & media</span></td>
                <td>
                  <ul class="topic-list">
                    <li>Star, mesh, hybrid layouts</li>
                    <li>UTP, STP, fiber basics</li>
                    <li>Connectors, transceivers, basic cabling rules</li>
                  </ul>
                </td>
                <td><span class="level-pill">Beginner</span></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><span class="module-label">1.3 Models & addressing</span></td>
                <td>
                  <ul class="topic-list">
                    <li>OSI and TCP IP models (layers & functions)</li>
                    <li>IPv4 structure, network & host part</li>
                    <li>IPv6 structure and advantages (high-level)</li>
                  </ul>
                </td>
                <td><span class="level-pill int">Intermediate</span></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><span class="module-label">1.4 Subnetting basics</span></td>
                <td>
                  <ul class="topic-list">
                    <li>Subnet mask and CIDR notation</li>
                    <li>Finding network ID, broadcast ID, usable hosts</li>
                    <li>Simple subnet design examples</li>
                  </ul>
                </td>
                <td><span class="level-pill int">Intermediate</span></td>
              </tr>
