          <!-- Module 4 -->
          <article class="card" id="module4">
            <h2>
              Module 4: IP Services (DHCP, NAT, QoS & more)
              <span class="badge">Services</span>
            </h2>
            <p>
              Learn common services required to run production networks and
              support users.
            </p>

            <table>
              <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Module</th>
                <th>Topics</th>
                <th>Level</th>
              </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td><span class="module-label">4.1 DHCP & name services</span></td>
                <td>
                  <ul class="topic-list">
                    <li>Dynamic address assignment concept</li>
                    <li>Basic relay idea for different networks</li>
                    <li>Role of name resolution in user connectivity</li>
                  </ul>
                </td>
                <td><span class="level-pill">Beginner</span></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><span class="module-label">4.2 NAT & PAT</span></td>
                <td>
                  <ul class="topic-list">
                    <li>Address translation concept and use cases</li>
                    <li>Inside and outside terminology</li>
                    <li>Static, dynamic and overload (port-based) examples</li>
                  </ul>
                </td>
                <td><span class="level-pill int">Intermediate</span></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><span class="module-label">4.3 NTP, logs & monitoring</span></td>
                <td>
                  <ul class="topic-list">
                    <li>Time synchronization basics</li>
                    <li>Log collection and importance for troubleshooting</li>
                    <li>High-level management with monitoring protocols</li>
                  </ul>
                </td>
                <td><span class="level-pill int">Intermediate</span></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><span class="module-label">4.4 QoS overview</span></td>
                <td>
                  <ul class="topic-list">
                    <li>Need for quality of service in networks</li>
                    <li>Classification, marking and queuing idea</li>
                    <li>Simple use cases such as voice traffic priority</li>
                  </ul>
                </td>
                <td><span class="level-pill adv">Advanced</span></td>
              </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </article>
        </div>

        <!-- Right: security, wireless, automation, troubleshooting -->
